## 1. Executive Summary

Semgrep detected several categories of issues, including:

- Hardcoded credentials and WiFi configuration literals.
- Hardcoded HTTP URLs (non-HTTPS).
- OTA update routes and filesystem admin routes.
- Files being opened/written/deleted in LittleFS.
- Use of OTA update APIs (`Update.begin`, `Update.write`, `Update.end`).
- WebSocket endpoint declaration.
- Inline `<script>` blocks in HTML files.
- C-style casts and `new` allocations in C++.
- PowerShell-related patterns (weak hashes, HTTP URLs, Invoke-Expression, etc.) in your PS rules/results.

This report is **static analysis only**. These are **findings to review**, not confirmed exploited vulnerabilities.

